{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GvZHbude44xea6kTV9ky9J","type":"tool_result","content":"112:- [ ] `game.settled` event type added to `EventTypes` in `event-types.ts`\n113:- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for coinflip rounds\n114:- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for lord (jackpot) rounds\n115:- [ ] `closecall-clock.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for closecall rounds\n116:- [ ] Event payload matches the schema above (all fields present, amounts as string-encoded lamports)\n117:- [ ] Existing settlement latency is not measurably affected (event is a single INSERT, no blocking)\n118:- [ ] Duplicate settlement retries may enqueue duplicate `game.settled` rows safely because downstream handlers dedupe on domain keys, not `event_queue.id`\n306:- [ ] Migration file `0XX_challenge_engine.sql` creates all tables above\n307:- [ ] All tables follow project conventions: BIGINT IDENTITY, CHECK constraints on TEXT enums, TIMESTAMPTZ, snake_case\n308:- [ ] `reward_config` seeded with default values on migration (see FR-13)\n309:- [ ] `reward_pool` seeded with single row (balance 0)\n310:- [ ] `reward_pool_fundings` provides idempotent, append-only pool funding records keyed by `round_id`\n311:- [ ] `point_grants` provides ledger-grade history for every points award path\n312:- [ ] Foreign key constraints enforced (challenges -> campaigns, assignments -> challenges, etc.)\n313:- [ ] Unique constraints prevent duplicate assignments, duplicate progress events, duplicate bonus completions, duplicate point grants, and duplicate crate drops\n314:- [ ] Indexes support the hot queries: active assignments by user, points history by user, pending crate drops, active dogpile events\n334:- [ ] Eligible settled-game processing emits one `points.grant` event per eligible player with a domain key derived from `(user_id, round_id, source_type='wager')`\n335:- [ ] `points.grant` handler calculates points for each player using `points_per_dollar` from `reward_config`\n336:- [ ] SOL/USD conversion uses the existing price service (cached, not per-event RPC)\n337:- [ ] Points awarded to both winners and losers in a settled game\n338:- [ ] Dogpile multiplier applied when a `dogpile_events` row is active at `settledAt` time\n339:- [ ] `point_grants` row inserted before `player_points.balance` and `lifetime_earned` are incremented atomically\n340:- [ ] `player_points` row created on first earn (upsert pattern)\n341:- [ ] Points calculation is deterministic and idempotent via `point_grants UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)`, not `progress_events`\n367:- [ ] Settled-round processing emits one `reward.pool_fund` event per round\n368:- [ ] `reward.pool_fund` handler calculates `floor(feeLamports * reward_pool_fee_share)` from config\n369:- [ ] `reward.pool_fund` handler dedupes on `round_id` via `reward_pool_fundings` before mutating `reward_pool`\n370:- [ ] `reward_pool.balance_lamports` incremented atomically within the handler's transaction\n371:- [ ] SOL crate payout calculated as `floor(balance * sol_crate_pool_pct)`\n372:- [ ] SOL crate suppressed (not created) when calculated payout < `sol_crate_min_value`\n373:- [ ] Reward pool remains accounting-only: no second on-chain fee split, no separate settlement-time wallet transfer\n374:- [ ] Pool balance never goes negative (payout subtracted only after validation)\n375:- [ ] `reward_pool.lifetime_funded` and `lifetime_paid` updated for audit/analytics\n376:- [ ] All pool operations happen within a serializable or row-locked transaction (no race conditions on balance)\n402:- [ ] Eligible settled-game processing emits one `crate.drop` event per eligible player after a `game.settled` event\n403:- [ ] Drop rates read from `reward_config` (`sol_crate_drop_rate`, `points_crate_drop_rate`)\n404:- [ ] SOL crate: `reward_pool` row locked (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`), balance checked, payout calculated, pool decremented, `crate_drops` row created — all in one transaction\n405:- [ ] SOL crate payout emits `crate.sol_payout` event for async SOL transfer\n406:- [ ] SOL crate suppressed when pool can't fund `sol_crate_min_value`\n407:- [ ] Points crate: random amount in configured range, `crate_drops` row created, `points.grant` emitted with `source_type = 'crate_points'`\n408:- [ ] `crate_drops` records trigger_type, trigger_id (round_id), crate_type, contents_amount\n409:- [ ] No crate drop for games that fail `quest_eligible()` check (FR-10)\n410:- [ ] Crate drop is idempotent per `(user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)` and enforced with a DB UNIQUE constraint\n427:- [ ] `dogpile_events` table supports scheduling events with start/end times and multiplier\n428:- [ ] Worker or cron transitions event status: scheduled -> active -> ended at the correct times\n429:- [ ] Points calculation in FR-3 reads active Dogpile event and applies multiplier\n430:- [ ] Active Dogpile check is a simple query: `SELECT multiplier FROM dogpile_events WHERE status = 'active' AND now() BETWEEN starts_at AND ends_at LIMIT 1`\n431:- [ ] Multiple Dogpile events cannot overlap; enforce via admin validation in M1 (DB exclusion constraint not required)\n432:- [ ] Dogpile events can be cancelled (status -> cancelled) before or during the window\n433:- [ ] `dogpile_active` and `dogpile_multiplier` are computed in handler context for analytics; they are not required fields on the `game.settled` payload\n470:- [ ] Adapter registry maps `action` string to adapter function\n471:- [ ] `game_completed` adapter: returns `shouldProgress: true` when game matches scope (or scope = 'any')\n472:- [ ] `game_won` adapter: returns `shouldProgress: true` when player `isWinner === true` and game matches scope\n473:- [ ] `lobby_filled` adapter: returns `shouldProgress: true` when `isCreator === true` and game settled normally\n474:- [ ] Each adapter is a pure function of (event, assignment, db) — no side effects beyond the returned result\n475:- [ ] Unknown adapter types log a warning and return `shouldProgress: false`\n500:- [ ] `game.settled` handler registered in the event queue handler registry\n501:- [ ] Handler iterates all players in the event payload\n502:- [ ] Quest eligibility check runs before any progress/points/crate processing\n503:- [ ] Active assignments loaded efficiently (indexed query on user_id + status = 'active')\n504:- [ ] Progress updates are atomic: INSERT progress_event + UPDATE assignment.progress in one transaction\n505:- [ ] Assignment status transitions to 'completed' when progress >= target\n506:- [ ] Challenge completion emits reward intents through the same downstream path as other rewards (`points.grant` with `source_type = 'challenge_completed'`, or `crate.drop` with `trigger_type = 'challenge_completed'`)\n507:- [ ] Points, crate, and pool-funding side-effects are emitted as separate reward events after challenge evaluation\n508:- [ ] `game.settled` handler is idempotent for progress and reward-event emission; downstream reward handlers are independently idempotent\n509:- [ ] Handler errors don't affect other players in the same event (per-player try/catch)\n510:- [ ] Processing time per event is bounded (< 100ms target for the DB operations)\n524:- [ ] Completion bonus check runs immediately after any assignment is marked completed\n525:- [ ] Count query: `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM challenge_assignments WHERE user_id = ? AND period_key = ? AND status = 'completed' AND challenge_id IN (SELECT id FROM challenges WHERE campaign_id = ?)`\n526:- [ ] Bonus completion is idempotent (UNIQUE on user_id, bonus_id, period_key)\n527:- [ ] Bonus reward (crate or points) is triggered via the same reward path as challenge rewards\n528:- [ ] Multiple bonuses can exist per campaign (future-proofing, but M1 has one per daily campaign)\n551:- [ ] `quest_eligible()` function implemented and called before all reward processing\n552:- [ ] Refunded games (`isWinner === null`) are excluded from challenge progress, points, and crate drops\n553:- [ ] Non-refund games continue through normal challenge/reward flow with no additional M1 gating\n554:- [ ] Ineligible games still settle normally (no impact on core game loop)\n555:- [ ] Any fraud flags implemented in M1 are advisory-only and do not silently change reward behavior\n580:- [ ] Daily challenges assigned lazily on first `GET /challenges/mine` call after 00:00 UTC\n581:- [ ] Weekly challenges assigned lazily on first call after Monday 00:00 UTC\n582:- [ ] `period_key` format: `daily:YYYY-MM-DD` for dailies, `weekly:YYYY-WNN` for weeklies\n583:- [ ] Assignment count matches campaign config (3 daily, 2 weekly for M1)\n584:- [ ] Challenges drawn from active challenges in the appropriate campaign\n585:- [ ] UNIQUE constraint prevents duplicate assignments for same user+challenge+period\n586:- [ ] Expired assignments are marked `expired` (either at query time or by cleanup worker)\n587:- [ ] Completion bonus for the daily campaign is checked when 3rd daily is completed\n609:- [ ] Onboarding campaign and 3 challenge templates seeded in migration or seed script\n610:- [ ] First onboarding step assigned on first `GET /challenges/mine` call for new users\n611:- [ ] Completing a step auto-assigns the next step (by `prerequisite_id`)\n612:- [ ] Onboarding assignments have `period_key = 'onboarding'` and no `expires_at`\n613:- [ ] Onboarding is one-time: once all steps completed, no further assignments\n614:- [ ] Onboarding challenges appear in `GET /challenges/mine` alongside daily/weekly\n639:- [ ] `reward_config` table seeded with all defaults above in the migration\n640:- [ ] Config values read by the engine at evaluation time (not cached beyond a single handler invocation)\n641:- [ ] Admin API endpoint `PUT /admin/reward-config/:key` updates a config value\n642:- [ ] Admin API endpoint `GET /admin/reward-config` returns all config values\n643:- [ ] 