// other dependencies\n}\n\nexport function createXxxHandler(deps: XxxDeps) {\n  const { db, ... } = deps;\n  \n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Handler logic\n  };\n}\n```\n- Handlers are dependency-injected (particularly `db` and utilities)\n- The factory returns an async function with no return value\n- Optional injectable dependencies (like `rollRng` in CRATE_DROP) enable testing\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n- **Transactions**: Both SOL and Points crate paths use `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity\n- **Idempotency**: Guarded by the UNIQUE constraint — duplicate events are silently skipped (no error)\n- **Event emission**: After successful crate creation, handlers emit follow-up events (e.g., `CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT` or `POINTS_GRANT`)\n- **Logging**: Structured logging with context (userId, triggerId, amounts) at each checkpoint\n\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/`."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66853f72-53c0-44d3-9075-63fb5cc11dbe","uuid":"313e2aa6-b3eb-42f5-a552-a64114a08a75","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:50:57.132Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files from the backend codebase to understand the existing patterns:\n\n1. backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/crate-drop.ts - existing crate drop handler\n2. backend/services/backend/src/index.ts - handler registration pattern\n3. backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts - event types\n\nI need to understand:\n- The CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT event type definition\n- How handlers are registered in index.ts\n- The crate_drops table columns (especially status field)\n- The factory pattern used for handlers\n\nRead full file contents and report back.\n\nThoroughness: medium","agentId":"a4614f6aa645dfbd9","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's my analysis of the existing patterns:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n#