d utilities)\n- The factory returns an async function with no return value\n- Optional injectable dependencies (like `rollRng` in CRATE_DROP) enable testing\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n- **Transactions**: Both SOL and Points crate paths use `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity\n- **Idempotency**: Guarded by the UNIQUE constraint — duplicate events are silently skipped (no error)\n- **Event emission**: After successful crate creation, handlers emit follow-up events (e.g., `CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT` or `POINTS_GRANT`)\n- **Logging**: Structured logging with context (userId, triggerId, amounts) at each checkpoint\n\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/`."}],"totalDurationMs":10456,"totalTokens":39065,"totalToolUseCount":3,"usage":{"input_tokens":288,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11125,"cache_read_input_tokens":26835,"output_tokens":817,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":11125},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
