{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ep59KwhN4Z9a7yPtuiTmv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## File Format and Structure\n\nThe `docs/TECH_DEBT.md` file follows this structure:\n\n**Overall Organization:**\n- Header: \"Technical Debt & Temporary Fixes\" with goal statement\n- Four priority sections separated by horizontal rules (---):\n  1. **High Priority (Fix ASAP)** - currently empty\n  2. **Medium Priority (Before Launch)** - items are strikethrough when resolved\n  3. **Low Priority (Post-Launch cleanup)** - currently empty\n  4. **Post-V1 Backlog (Revisit When More Advanced)** - detailed items for future work\n\n**Entry Format (for detailed items like Post-V1 Backlog):**\n```\n### [Category] Title of Issue\n- **Date**: YYYY-MM-DD\n- **Location**: file path or component reference\n- **What**: Description of the problem/hack\n- **Current mitigation**: How it's currently handled\n- **Proper solution**: What the right fix should be (numbered steps optional)\n- **Why not now**: Justification for deferring\n```\n\n**Entry Format (for simpler items like Medium Priority):**\n```\n### ~~[Category] Issue Title~~\n- **Resolved**: YYYY-MM-DD — Brief explanation of resolution\n```\n\n**Key conventions:**\n- Items are prefixed with `[Category]` in brackets (e.g., `[Jackpot]`, `[On-Chain]`)\n- Use strikethrough (`~~text~~`) to mark resolved items\n- Include date for tracking\n- Structured metadata fields using bold markdown (`**Field Name**:`)\n\nTo add a new entry, choose the appropriate priority section and follow the format matching that section's style."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66853f72-53c0-44d3-9075-63fb5cc11dbe","uuid":"95d16835-7b4a-45e9-93ca-0c1b02c7b9de","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:50:59.368Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file docs/TECH_DEBT.md to understand its format and where to add a new entry. Quick search. Report the file format/structure.\n\nThorou