{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RoQxTEdAdP9h7dahh799eR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Complete Analysis of the Referral-Claim Handler\n\nI've found and analyzed the complete implementation of the referral claim handler. Here's the full breakdown:\n\n### 1. **SOL Transfer Pattern (web3.js functions)**\n\nThe handler uses the standard Solana web3.js pattern:\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (lines 95-122)\n\n```\n- Connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\") → Get fresh blockhash with block height\n- new Transaction() → Create transaction with feePayer, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight\n- SystemProgram.transfer() → Add transfer instruction from server keypair to recipient\n- transaction.sign(serverKeypair) → Sign with server keypair\n- connection.sendRawTransaction() → Send raw serialized transaction with skipPreflight: false\n- connection.confirmTransaction() → Wait for \"confirmed\" commitment with blockhash and lastValidBlockHeight\n- Check confirmation.value.err for transaction errors\n```\n\nThe amount is passed as `Number(lamports)` to SystemProgram.transfer.\n\n### 2. **Handler Structure (Factory Pattern + Dependency Injection)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (lines 25-183)\n\n**Pattern**: Factory function with dependency injection\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  // Returns an async handler function\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => { ... }\n}\n```\n\nThe handler is created once at startup and reused for all events.\n\n### 3. **Success/Failure Handling**\n\n**Three-tier status system**:\n\n1. **Permanent Failures** (marked as `\"failed\"`):\n   - Insufficient balance (line 76-88)\n   - Max retries exceeded (line 145)\n\n2. **Transient Errors** (marked as `\"error\"`, retryable):\n   - Network errors, transaction failures\n   - Increments retry_count and re-throws exception (lines 139-181)\n\n3. **Idempotency Checks**:\n   - If status is already `\"completed\"` → return early (lines 53-58)\n   - If status is already `\"failed\"` → return early (lines 60-65)\n   - If claim not found → return early as no-op (lines 47-51)\n\n**Retry Logic**: On transient error:\n- Increments retry counter\n- Checks if `retry_count + 1 >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES` (5)\n- If final retry: sets status to `\"failed\"` and doesn't rethrow\n- Otherwise: rethrows to allow queue worker's exponential backoff\n\n### 4. **Handler Registration**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 216-219)\n\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n**Registration System Files**:\n- Registry: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (simple Map<string, EventHandler>)\n- Event types: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n- Worker: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Handler is registered once at server startup\n2. Event queue worker polls the `event_queue` table every 1500ms (default)\n3. Claims events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` for safe concurrency\n4. Looks up handler via `getHandler(event_type)`\n5. Executes handler with event payload\n6. On success: marks event as `\"completed\"`\n7. On error: increments attempts, schedules retry with exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s), or marks as `\"dead\"` if max attempts exceeded\n\n### Summary of Key Implementation Details\n\n- **SOL transfers**: Raw transaction construction with `SystemProgram.transfer`, explicit signing, and confirmation waiting\n- **Dependencies injected**: db, connection, serverKeypair passed in at creation\n- **Idempotent by design**: Multiple checks for already-completed or already-failed claims\n- **Two-level retry**: Handler's own retry_count (up to 5) + queue worker's exponential backoff\n- **Factory + registry pattern**: Handler factories registered at startup, queue worker looks them up by string event type\n- **Permanent vs transient failures**: Insufficient balance is permanent; network errors are transient with retries"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66853f72-53c0-44d3-9075-63fb5cc11dbe","uuid":"562f417e-add8-4faf-9324-fdd9d6c23953","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:51:36.192Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the referral-claim handler in the backend. I need to understand the exact pattern used for SOL transfers. Look in:\n- backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/ for referral-claim.ts or similar\n- Also look for any SOL transfer patterns (sendAndConfirmTransaction, SystemProgram.transfer, etc.)\n\nRead the full file content and report back the complete implementation pattern, especially:\n1. How SOL transfers are done (what web3.js functions are used)\n2. How the handler is structured (factory pattern? deps injection?)\n3. How success/failure are handled\n4. How the handler is registered\n\nThoroughness: medium","agentId":"a5dcbe9c7e1ea6fc8","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Complete Analysis of the Referral-Claim Handler\n\nI've found and analyzed the complete implementation of the referral claim handler. Here's the full breakdown:\n\n### 1. **SOL Transfer Pattern (web3.js functions)**\n\nThe handler uses the standard Solana web3.js pattern:\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (lines 95-122)\n\n```\n- Connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\") → Get fresh blockhash with block height\n- new Transaction() → Create transaction with feePayer, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight\n- SystemProgram.transfer() → Add transfer instruction from server keypair to recipient\n- transaction.sign(serverKeypair) → Sign with server keypair\n- connection.sendRawTransaction() → Send raw serialized transaction with skipPreflight: false\n- connection.confirmTransaction() → Wait for \"confirmed\" commitment with blockhash and lastValidBlockHeight\n- Check confirmation.value.err for transaction errors\n```\n\nThe amount is passed as `Number(lamports)` to SystemProgram.transfer.\n\n### 2. **Handler Structure (Factory Pattern + Dependency Injection)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (lines 25-183)\n\n**Pattern**: Factory function with dependency injection\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  // Returns an async handler function\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => { ... }\n}\n```\n\nThe handler is created once at startup and reused for all events.\n\n### 3. **Success/Failure Handling**\n\n**Three-tier status system**:\n\n1. **Permanent Failures** (marked as `\"failed\"`):\n   - Insufficient balance (line 76-88)\n   - Max retries exceeded (line 145)\n\n2. **Transient Errors** (marked as `\"error\"`, retryable):\n   - Network errors, transaction failures\n   - Increments retry_count and re-throws exception (lines 139-181)\n\n3. **Idempotency Checks**:\n   - If status is already `\"completed\"` → return early (lines 53-58)\n   - If status is already `\"failed\"` → return early (lines 60-65)\n   - If claim not found → return early as no-op (lines 47-51)\n\n**Retry Logic**: On transient error:\n- Increments retry counter\n- Checks if `retry_count + 1 >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES` (5)\n- If final retry: sets status to `\"failed\"` and doesn't rethrow\n- Otherwise: rethrows to allow queue worker's exponential backoff\n\n### 4. **Handler Registration**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 216-219)\n\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n**Registration System Files**:\n- Registry: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (simple Map<string, EventHandler>)\n- Event types: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n- Worker: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Handler is registered once at server startup\n2. Event queue worker polls the `event_queue` table every 1500ms (default)\n3. Claims events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` for safe concurrency\n4. Looks up handler via `getHandler(event_type)`\n5. Executes handler with event payload\n6. On success: marks event as `\"completed\"`\n7. On error: increments attempts, schedules retry with exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s), or marks as `\"dead\"` if max attempts exceeded\n\n### Summary of Key Implementation Details\n\n- **SOL transfers**: Raw transaction construction with `SystemProgram.transfer`, explicit signing, and confirmation waiting\n- **Dependencies injected**: db, connection, serverKeypair passed in at creation\n- **Idempotent by design**: Multiple checks for already-completed or already-failed claims\n- **Two-level retry**: Handler's own retry_count (up to 5) + queue worker's exponential backoff\n- **Factory + registry pattern**: Handler factories registered at startup, queue worker looks them up by string event type\n- **Permanent vs transient failures**: Insufficient balance is permanent; network errors are transient with retries"}],"totalDurationMs":52800,"totalTokens":43620,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":366,"cache_read_input_tokens":42030,"output_tokens":1218,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":366},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
