m the referral claim handler, which uses a `claimId` to load the specific record. So I need to include `crateDropId` in the event payload and load by ID. This means modifying `insertCrateDrop` to return `string | null`, updating the SOL path to include `crateDropId` in the CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT event, and creating a new handler that loads by `crateDropId`. It's a minimal change that follows the established pattern.\n\nNow I need to check the config to see how `config.serverKeypair` and the Connection are set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2196,"cache_read_input_tokens":60506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2196},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66853f72-53c0-44d3-9075-63fb5cc11dbe","uuid":"c2f68cbb-fbdb-4bbd-9c7c-86894825bd6e"}
